div1.p: Territory of Washington County of Spokane } SS
In the matter of George Woodard
The territory of Washington vs. George Woodard
To James Glispie Sheriff of Spokan County.

In the name of the United States we command you that you leave the body of George Woodard, by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention by whoever name said George Woodard shall be called or charged before Honorable George Turner. Judge of the District court of the Fourth justice district of the territory of Wahington at this Chambers in the city of Spokane Falls in Spokane County on
the 9th day of July A.D. 1887 at the hour of ten O'Clock A.M. to do and recive what shall then and there be considered of him the said George Woodard and have you then and there this Writ.
Witness the Honorable George Turner, judge of the said court, and the seal there of affixed this 8th day of July A.D. 1887
Territory of Wshington County of Spokane } ss
I hereby certify that by witness of the returned writ have the body of Geo Woodard now In court in custody as directed by the returned writ On Dates July 9th A D 1887
Jas Glispie Sheriff of Sopokane County
